posts.title: Why The Devil Wears Prada 2 Is Everywhere
posts.excerpt: Nostalgia + pacing + a shareable hook = instant lift.
article: This video taps directly into nostalgia while feeling modern enough to share.
The hook lands fast, so people don’t bounce in the first 3 seconds.
It’s built for group chats: easy premise, quick payoff.

posts.title: The Psychology of Getting Rich
posts.excerpt: Why money is less about strategy and more about identity, belief, and behavior.
article: This video breaks down wealth as a psychological game rather than a tactical one.
The core idea is simple: people stay broke because their identity is wired for safety, not growth.
Instead of chasing hacks, the video reframes money as a reflection of standards, self-image, and decision-making speed.
notes: Identity drives behavior more than motivation.
Wealth grows faster when decisions are made quickly and confidently.

posts.title: Arsenal vs Chelsea: Carabao Cup Semi-Final Breakdown
posts.excerpt: A tense Carabao Cup semi-final as Arsenal protect a narrow lead heading into the second leg.
article: This match highlights Arsenal’s ability to control tempo in high-pressure knockout games.
Chelsea struggled to break lines consistently, relying heavily on wide play and transitions.
The tactical discipline shown here explains why Arsenal have become difficult to beat in cup competitions.
notes: Game control matters more than possession.
Momentum shifts are decided in the first 20 minutes.

posts.title: Top Richest YouTubers of 2025
posts.excerpt: A breakdown of the highest-earning YouTubers in 2025 and how creator wealth is actually built.
article: This video highlights how YouTube wealth is rarely about views alone.
Most top earners combine ads, brand deals, businesses, and equity stakes.
The biggest takeaway is that distribution beats talent when it comes to scale.
notes: YouTube is a traffic source, not the business.

posts.title: I Make $2.4M a Year With 6 YouTube Channels
posts.excerpt: How building multiple niche YouTube channels compounds revenue faster than relying on a single brand.
article: This video breaks the myth that you need one massive channel to win on YouTube.
The strategy focuses on systems, delegation, and repeatable formats.
Multiple channels reduce platform risk while increasing total surface area for monetization.
notes: Niche channels scale faster than personality brands.
YouTube becomes infrastructure, not the product.
